    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-11-01T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-11-01T04:00:00-05:00" n="258"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                <head>258. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    Station in Saigon to the Director of the National Security Agency (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BLGGA1" type="to">Blake</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d258fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 26 <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> VIET
                        Secret; Flash The source text is the copy sent for information Flash to the
                        Department of State. Also sent Flash to <gloss target="#t_USIB1"
                            >USIB</gloss> agencies. Received at the Department of State at 4:11
                        a.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1963-11-01T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1963, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. <gloss target="#t_DTG1">DTG</gloss> 0-00Z. Conein at <gloss target="#t_JGS1"
                        >JGS</gloss> reports <persName corresp="#p_DVBMMG1">Big Minh</persName>
                    called President on telephone but President allegedly not present and <persName
                        corresp="#p_DVBMMG1">Big Minh</persName> spoke to <persName
                        corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName>. In order show strength all Gens present
                    including in addition to those previously named, Gen La, Gen Tam, Gen Oai, and
                    Gen Ngoc. In addition, Col Lam of the <gloss target="#t_CG1">CG</gloss>, Col
                    Khang of the Marines and Col Khuong also spoke to <persName corresp="#p_NHU1"
                        >Nhu</persName> on the telephone. In addition, Col <persName
                        corresp="#p_TUNG1">Tung</persName> was forced at gun point to announce that
                    he a prisoner. Air Force Commander did not speak. Conein believes he has been
                    eliminated. <persName corresp="#p_DVBMMG1">Big Minh</persName> stated to
                        <persName corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName> that if the President and
                        <persName corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName> did not resign, turn themselves
                    over to the coup forces within five minutes, the Palace will sustain a massive
                    airborne bombardment. At this, Gen <persName corresp="#p_MINH1">Minh</persName>
                    hung up.<note n="2" xml:id="d258fn2">
                        <p>In the next telegram in this series, <gloss target="#t_CAS1">CAS</gloss>
                            Saigon 3, <gloss target="#t_DTG1">DTG</gloss> 0-21Z, November 1, the
                            Station relayed the following information on a second <persName
                                corresp="#p_DVBMMG1">Big Minh</persName>-<persName
                                corresp="#p_DIEM1">Diem</persName> telephone conversation:</p>
                        <p>“Conein reports from <gloss target="#t_JGS1">JGS</gloss> that Gen
                                <persName corresp="#p_DVBMMG1">Big Minh</persName> once more called
                            President <persName corresp="#p_DIEM1">Diem</persName> and <persName
                                corresp="#p_DIEM1">Diem</persName> hung up as of 1715 hours.
                                <persName corresp="#p_MINH1">Minh</persName> has given the order to
                            bomb the Palace. This apparently refutes radio announcements that
                            President has resigned which broadcasted approx 1710 hr.” (<hi
                                rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.)</p>
                    </note>
                </p>
            </div>
